				</a>
				<a
					href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/spencer-fletcher-890b19237"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
					aria-label="LinkedIn Profile"
				>
					<img src="/linkedin.png" height="24" width="24" alt="" />
				</a>
			</footer>
		</div>
	</body>

	<style is:global>
		/* Using is:global for simplicity, as this is the main page component.
      You could also move this to a separate .css file and import it.
    */
		:root {
			--bg-color: #7877e6;
			--text-color: #ffffff;
			--tag-bg: #5d5cb6; /* A slightly darker shade for contrast */
			--font-family: "Open Sans", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI",
				Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, "Apple Color Emoji",
				"Segoe UI Emoji", "Segoe UI Symbol";
		}

		body {
			background-color: var(--bg-color);
			color: var(--text-color);
			font-family: var(--font-family);
			margin: 0;
			padding: 2rem 2rem;
			display: flex;
			justify-content: center;
			line-height: 1.6;
		}

		* {
			margin: 0;
		}

		.container {
			max-width: 900px;
			width: 100%;
		}

		h1,
		h2,
		h3,
		h4,
		h5,
		h6 {
			font-weight: 600;
		}

		h1 {
			font-size: 2.5rem;
			margin-bottom: -0.5rem;
		}

		h3 {
			margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		}

		.subtitle {
			font-size: 1.5rem;
			margin-top: 0;
			font-weight: 300;
			opacity: 0.9;
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 2rem;
			margin-bottom: 0;
		}

		h3 {
			font-size: 1.25rem;
		}

		a {
			color: var(--text-color);
			text-decoration: underline;
			font-weight: 500;
		}

		a:hover {
			text-decoration: none;
		}

		/* Tools Section */
		.tools-grid {
			display: grid;
			/* Create 3 columns on desktop, stacking on mobile */
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
			gap: 1.5rem;
		}

		.tools-grid ul {
			list-style: none;
			padding: 0;
			margin: 0;
		}

		.tools-grid li {
			margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		}

		/* Projects Section */
		/* ...and CHANGE it to this. We just need to remove the margin. */
		.projects article {
			/* margin-bottom is no longer needed, 'gap' will handle it */
		}

		/* ADD these new rules for the flex container and items */
		.projects-container {
			display: flex;
			flex-wrap: wrap; /* This is key to "shrinking" to 1 column */
			gap: 1.5rem; /* This replaces your old margin-bottom */
		}

		.projects-container article {
			/* This is the magic rule.
      - flex-grow: 1 (items can grow to fill extra space)
      - flex-shrink: 1 (items can shrink)
      - flex-basis: 200px (items *want* to be 200px wide)
      
      On your 900px wide container, this will fit 4 articles per row (4 * 200px + gaps).
      On a narrow mobile screen, 200px won't fit, so 'flex-wrap' will 
      force each article onto its own line, creating your 1-column stack.
    */
			flex: 1 1 400px;
		}

		.tags {
			display: flex;
			flex-wrap: wrap;
			gap: 0.5rem;
			margin: 1rem 0;
		}

		.tag {
			background-color: var(--tag-bg);
			padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
			border-radius: 1rem;
			font-size: 0.875rem;
			font-weight: 500;
		}

		.links {
			display: flex;
			flex-wrap: wrap;
			gap: 1.5rem;
		}

		.note {
			font-style: italic;
			opacity: 0.8;
			font-size: 0.9rem;
		}

		p {
			margin-bottom: 0rem;
		}

		main {
			margin-top: 2rem;
		}

		section {
			margin-bottom: 4rem;
		}

		h2 {
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
		}

		header {
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
			display: flex;
			flex-wrap: wrap; /* Allows buttons to stack on small screens */
			justify-content: space-between;
			align-items: center;
			gap: 1.5rem; /* Adds space between title and buttons, especially when stacked */
		}

		.social-links {
			display: flex;
			justify-content: center;
			gap: 2rem;
			margin-top: 5rem;
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
		}

		.social-links a {
			text-decoration: none;
		}

		/* Style the <img> tags */
		.social-links img {
			width: 32px;
			height: 32px;
			opacity: 0.8;
			transition: opacity 0.2s ease;

			/* This filter forces the images to be white, matching the text */
			filter: brightness(0) invert(1);
		}

		.social-links a:hover img {
			opacity: 1;
		}

		/* --- Header CTA Buttons --- */

		.header-cta {
			display: flex;
			gap: 1rem; /* Space between the two buttons */
			flex-shrink: 0; /* Prevents buttons from shrinking awkwardly */
		}

		.cta-button {
			display: inline-block;
			padding: 0.65rem 1.25rem;
			border-radius: 8px; /* Rounded corners */
			text-decoration: none;
			font-weight: 600;
			font-size: 0.9rem;
			transition: all 0.2s ease;
			border: 2px solid var(--text-color);
			line-height: 1.2;
		}

		/* Primary button style (Email) */
		.cta-button {
			background-color: var(--text-color);
			color: var(--bg-color); /* Inverted colors */
		}

		.cta-button:hover {
			background-color: transparent;
			color: var(--text-color);
			text-decoration: none;
		}

		/* Secondary "ghost" button style (Resume) */
		.cta-button-secondary {
			background-color: transparent;
			color: var(--text-color);
		}

		.cta-button-secondary:hover {
			background-color: var(--text-color);
			color: var(--bg-color); /* Inverted on hover */
			text-decoration: none;
		}

		/* Responsive adjustments */
		@media (min-width: 768px) {
			body {
				padding: 3rem;
			}
			.tools-grid {
				/* Force 3 columns on larger screens */
				grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
			}
		}

		.about p:first-child {
			margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
		}
	</style>
</html>
